--- body ---
## Problem

Housekeeping runs `git fsck --unreachable` on every beat to count dangling commits.
On large repos (Climate_finance: ~2100 commits) this is slow and its output (a count)
adds nothing actionable — housekeeping never acts on unreachable commits.

## Solution

Remove the `git fsck --unreachable` call from the healthcheck skill.
Replace with `git gc --auto 2>/dev/null || true` if GC hygiene is desired
(gc --auto is a no-op unless the pack threshold is exceeded).

## Acceptance criteria

- healthcheck skill no longer calls git fsck
- No regression in detecting actual repo problems (corrupt objects, broken refs)
- git gc --auto added if desired, otherwise removed entirely

## Effort

Very low — one-line skill prompt / Bash change.

## Actions (planned)

1. `skills/healthcheck/SKILL.md` line 22: delete check #6 "Orphan commits — count unreachable commits"
2. Same file line 45: delete "Orphan commits" row from the output table
3. Renumber checks 7→6, 8→7, 9→8
4. Do NOT add `git gc --auto` — not needed, out of scope
5. Run tests, validate tickets, commit
